<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8">
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
    <title>Qwen Coder Prompt - Premium LMS</title>
    <script src="https://cdn.tailwindcss.com"></script>
    <link href="https://fonts.googleapis.com/css2?family=Plus+Jakarta+Sans:wght@400;500;600;700&display=swap" rel="stylesheet">
    <style>
        body {
            font-family: 'Plus Jakarta Sans', sans-serif;
            background-color: #f8fafc;
        }
        .prompt-container {
            max-width: 900px;
            margin: 40px auto;
            background: white;
            border-radius: 24px;
            box-shadow: 0 10px 25px -5px rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.1), 0 8px 10px -6px rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.1);
            overflow: hidden;
            border: 1px solid #e2e8f0;
        }
        .code-block {
            background-color: #0f172a;
            color: #e2e8f0;
            padding: 24px;
            border-radius: 12px;
            font-family: 'Fira Code', monospace;
            font-size: 14px;
            line-height: 1.6;
            position: relative;
        }
        .copy-button {
            position: absolute;
            top: 12px;
            right: 12px;
            background: #3b82f6;
            color: white;
            padding: 6px 12px;
            border-radius: 6px;
            font-size: 12px;
            cursor: pointer;
            transition: all 0.2s;
        }
        .copy-button:hover {
            background: #2563eb;
        }
    </style>
</head>
<body class="p-6">

    <div class="prompt-container">
        <div class="p-8 border-b border-slate-100 bg-slate-50/50">
            <div class="flex items-center gap-3 mb-2">
                <span class="px-3 py-1 bg-blue-100 text-blue-700 text-xs font-bold rounded-full uppercase tracking-wider">High-End Engineering</span>
            </div>
            <h1 class="text-3xl font-bold text-slate-900 mb-2">Qwen Coder "Sea Dog" Prompt</h1>
            <p class="text-slate-600">Copy the code below and paste it directly into Qwen Coder to generate your professional Course Management System.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="p-8">
            <div class="relative code-block">
                <button onclick="copyPrompt()" class="copy-button" id="copyBtn">Copy Prompt</button>
                <pre id="promptText" class="whitespace-pre-wrap">Act as a Senior Full-Stack Developer and UI/UX Architect. I need you to build a highly modern, professional Course Management Dashboard. 

### TECHNICAL STACK REQUIREMENTS:
- Format: Single-file HTML5 solution (Production-ready).
- Styling: Tailwind CSS (via Play CDN).
- Icons: Lucide Icons.
- Fonts: "Plus Jakarta Sans" or "Inter".
- Logic: Vanilla JS/Alpine.js for state (tab switching, modal toggles, search filtering).

### VISUAL DESIGN SYSTEM:
- Palette: "Deep Midnight" (#0F172A), "Electric Indigo" (#6366F1), and "Ghost White" (#F8FAFC).
- Aesthetic: Enterprise SaaS. Large border radii (20px+), soft multi-layered shadows, and glassmorphism for the sidebar.
- Logo/Mascot: The brand is "Sea Dog". Integrate a stylized "Sea Dog" mascot (a dog wearing a captain's hat or nautical gear) using a high-quality SVG or an &lt;img&gt; placeholder that looks aesthetic.

### DASHBOARD COMPONENTS:
1. Sidebar: Collapsible navigation with active state indicators.
2. Top Bar: Search input, Notification bell with badge, and User Profile (with Sea Dog avatar).
3. Stats Row: 4 cards (Total Students, Courses, Completion Rate, Revenue) using micro-animations.
4. Course Table/Grid: Professional list featuring:
   - Course Thumbnail
   - Status badges (Active, Draft, Archived)
   - Progress bars for student engagement
   - "Quick Action" buttons (Edit, Analytics, Delete).
5. "Create Course" Modal: A sleek slide-over form with smooth transitions.

### DEPLOYMENT SPECIFICATIONS:
- The code must be fully self-contained.
- All assets (CSS, JS, Fonts) must be linked via secure HTTPS CDNs.
- Optimize the layout for GitHub Pages deployment.

Ensure the code is clean, semantic, and commented. Build it like a $100k custom LMS platform.</pre>
            </div>

            <div class="mt-8 grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-2 gap-4">
                <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-slate-200 bg-white">
                    <h3 class="font-bold text-slate-800 flex items-center gap-2">
                        <span>ðŸš€</span> Step 1
                    </h3>
                    <p class="text-sm text-slate-500 mt-1">Paste the prompt into Qwen Coder and wait for the HTML generation.</p>
                </div>
                <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-slate-200 bg-white">
                    <h3 class="font-bold text-slate-800 flex items-center gap-2">
                        <span>ðŸ“‚</span> Step 2
                    </h3>
                    <p class="text-sm text-slate-500 mt-1">Save the output as <b>index.html</b> and upload it to your GitHub repository.</p>
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>

    <script>
        function copyPrompt() {
            const text = document.getElementById('promptText').innerText;
            navigator.clipboard.writeText(text).then(() => {
                const btn = document.getElementById('copyBtn');
                btn.innerText = 'Copied!';
                btn.style.background = '#10b981';
                setTimeout(() => {
                    btn.innerText = 'Copy Prompt';
                    btn.style.background = '#3b82f6';
                }, 2000);
            });
        }
    </script>

</body>
</html>
